<h2 class="pen"><a rel="bookmark" https://yarnetsky.github.io/ontheriversedge/index.php?id=957" title="Permanent link to this article">Mother Nature vs. Dubya</a></h2>

<div class="post">

<div class="entrytext">

	<p>My father-in-law who lives outside of Lima, Ohio, reports that Dubya was speaking there today.</p>

	<p>He watched Bush on the local Lima station speaking at the new high school when a huge storm rolled in and knocked out the power toward the end of his speech.</p>

	<p>He then apparently couldn&#8217;t get out of town on the pre-planned blockade route because of flash-flooding as more than 2 inches of rain fell in 15 minutes.</p>

	<p>Hmmm&#8230;. is mother nature trying to tell us something? Don&#8217;t we wish. Anyway it&#8217;d be lost on Lima which is very Republican&#8212;so much so that every Republican nominee has visited the town.</p>

	<p>You can access the paper&#8217;s website at <a href="http://www.limanews.com">LimaNews.com</a> Unfortunately, the site didn&#8217;t work quite right with my Mac browser so I couldn&#8217;t verify the information with the paper.</p>



 

<p class="postmetadata alt">

<small>This entry was posted on Aug 29 by <a https://yarnetsky.github.io/ontheriversedge/index.php?author=E.G.+Yarnetsky">E.G. Yarnetsky</a>. You can skip to the end and leave a response using the comment form.</small></p>

</div>

</div>




	

	<p>

